HEADWORD: Yellow-covered
<hw>Yel"low-cov`ered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Covered or
bound in yellow paper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Yellow-covered literature</b></col>, <cd>cheap
sensational novels and trashy magazines; -- formerly so called from the
usual color of their covers.</cd> <mark>[Colloq. U. S.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj> </cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

